    "Contents of cultural evolutionary science include observation statements, methodological commitments, presuppositions about varieties of statistical tests, and more.",
    "'Cultural evolutionary theory' ('CET') refers to the subset of cultural evolutionary science composing laws, generalizations and hypotheses, and their derivations and entailments.",
    "The events, processes and objects in the world that physically and mentally instantiate the transmission and evolution of culture across persons, populations and generations we refer to simply as 'cultural evolution' or 'cultural evolutionary processes'.",
